# Sharix API
The Sharix API is for those interested in playing millions of movies and shows in your application. The Sharix API can be used to retrieve and use data and/or sources programmatically.

# Legal Disclaimer
The Sharix API and the distribution of the Sharix API is not illegal and does not violate DMCA laws. However, use of the Sharix API may be illegal in your region. Check your local laws and regulations regarding the playback of potentially copyrighted content. The operators will not tolerate the Sharix API being used for anything illegal in any state, region, country or planet. Please use the Sharix API at your own risk.

# Sharix TV App
The Sharix API has been fully implemented in the [**Sharix TV App**](https://sharix.tech) which runs across all devices. These include iOS, iPadOS, tvOS, macOS and Airplay.

# Status 
The status of the Sharix API services can be checked at [**status.sharix.tech**](https://status.sharix.tech).

# Issues 
If you encounter problems using the Sharix API or the documentation is incomplete or incorrect, please file a issue on [**GitHub**](https://github.com/Boostvolt/sharix_tv_api/issues).

# API URL
The API should always be accessed over SSL.

```
https://api.sharix.tech
```

# Verbs
The API uses restful verbs.

| Verb | Description |
|---|---|
| `GET` | Select one or more items. Success returns `200` status code. |

# Dates
All dates will be GMT and returned in the ISO 8601 format like `2020-09-01T09:10:11.000Z`. Adjust accordingly in your app for the user's local timezone.

# Media Links
There are several ways to construct direct links to media on the Sharix API website. The website itself uses slugs so the URLs are more readable.

| Type | URL |
|---|---|
| `movie` | `/movies/:slug` |
| `show` | `/shows/:slug` |

# Data Structures

## Movie
_id: (string, required)
imdb_id: (string, required)
title: (string, required)
year: (number, required)
slug: (string, optional)
synopsis: (string, required)
runtime: (number, required)
released: (number,  required)
trailer: (string,  required)
certification: (string,  required)
clusters: (MovieLanguages, required)
genres: (array[string], required)
images: (Images, required)
rating: (Rating, required)
type: (string, required)
language: (string,  optional)

# Group Movies

## All [/movies]

### Get all movies [GET]
Returns an array of all available movies.

  + Request (application/json)

      + Headers

            sharix-api-authorization:[access_token]
            sharix-api-version: 1
            
  + Response 200 (application/json; charset=utf-8)

      + Body

            ["movies/1","movies/2","movies/3","movies/4","movies/5","movies/6","movies/7","movies/8","movies/9","movies/10"]

      + Attributes (array[string])

